      "url": "https://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2026/05/260511213144.htm",
      "title": "[ScienceDaily] Scientists reversed biological age in older adults with a 4-week diet change",
      "content_html": "<img src=\"https://www.sciencedaily.com/images/1920/woman-anti-aging-beauty-treatment-face-close-up.webp\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\nA four-week diet change was enough to make some older adults appear biologically younger in a new University of Sydney study. Participants who reduced fat intake or shifted toward more plant-based protein showed improvements in key health biomarkers tied to aging. The strongest results came from a lower-fat, higher-carb diet, while people eating closer to their usual diets saw almost no change.",
